{"title_page": "Peter Bakker", "text_new": "{{for|the Dutch rower|Peter Bakker (rower)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Peter Bakker\n| image = Flickr - World Economic Forum - Peter Bakker - Annual Meeting of the New Champions Tianjin 2008.jpg\n| caption = Peter Bakker at a Press Conference in 2008\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1961|08|1|df=y}}\n| nationality = Dutch\n| alma_mater = [[Inholland University of Applied Sciences]], [[Erasmus University Rotterdam]]\n| title = President of the [[World Business Council for Sustainable Development]]\n| spouse = [[Merel Bakker]] (2012\u2013present)\n| children = 3\n}}\n'''Peter Bakker''' (born 1 August 1961) is a Dutch businessman who currently serves as president of the [[World Business Council for Sustainable Development]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://president.wbcsd.org/about-peter-bakker.html|title=About Peter Bakker|website=WBCSD President|access-date=18 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nBakker has a master's degree in Economics from [[Erasmus University Rotterdam]] and a bachelor's degree in Business Administration from [[Inholland University of Applied Sciences]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\nBakker was appointed President of WBCSD in January 2012 after being CEO of [[TNT N.V.]] for 10 years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/wbcsd-announces-new-president-peter-bakker|title=WBCSD announces new president|last=Council|first=World Business|date=15 September 2011|newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=18 February 2017|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He is also the Chairman for [[War Child (charity)|War Child Netherlands]], Deputy Chairman for International Integrated Reporting Council and a Co-Chair in the Sustainable Developments Solution Network.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/author/peter-bakker|title=Peter Bakker {{!}} The Huffington Post|website=www.huffingtonpost.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=18 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Other activities ==\n* [[Nespresso]], Member of the Sustainability Advisory Board (NSAB)<ref>{{cite web|title=Nespresso Sustainability Advisory Board|url=https://www.nestle-nespresso.com/sustainability/sustainability-advisory-board/board-members}}</ref>\n* [[Daimler AG|Daimler]], Member of the Advisory Board for Integrity and Corporate Responsibility<ref>[https://www.daimler.com/sustainability/basics/integrity/the-advisory-board-for-integrity.html Advisory Board for Integrity and Corporate Responsibility] [[Daimler AG|Daimler]].</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nBakker was awarded the [[Clinton Global Citizen Award]] in 2009 and the [[Sustainable Asset Management|SAM]] Sustainability Leadership Award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://cbey.yale.edu/our-community/peter-bakker|title=Peter Bakker|date=17 September 2015|newspaper=The Center for Business and the Environment at Yale|access-date=18 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nBakker married Merel Bakker in 2012.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bakker, Peter}}\n[[Category:Dutch chief executives]]\n[[Category:Erasmus University Rotterdam alumni]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sustainability advocates]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Dutch rower|Peter Bakker (rower)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Peter Bakker\n| image = Flickr - World Economic Forum - Peter Bakker - Annual Meeting of the New Champions Tianjin 2008.jpg\n| caption = Peter Bakker at a Press Conference in 2008\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1961|08|1|df=y}}\n| nationality = Dutch\n| alma_mater = [[Inholland University of Applied Sciences]], [[Erasmus University Rotterdam]]\n| title = President of the [[World Business Council for Sustainable Development]]\n| spouse = [[Merel Bakker]] (2012\u2013present)\n| children = 3\n}}\n'''Peter Bakker''' (born 1 August 1961) is a Dutch businessman who currently serves as president of the [[World Business Council for Sustainable Development]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://president.wbcsd.org/about-peter-bakker.html|title=About Peter Bakker|website=WBCSD President|access-date=18 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nBakker has a master's degree in Economics from [[Erasmus University Rotterdam]] and a bachelor's degree in Business Administration from [[Inholland University of Applied Sciences]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\nBakker was appointed President of WBCSD in January 2012 after being CEO of [[TNT N.V.]] for 10 years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/wbcsd-announces-new-president-peter-bakker|title=WBCSD announces new president|last=Council|first=World Business|date=15 September 2011|newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=18 February 2017|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He is also the Chairman for [[War Child (charity)|War Child Netherlands]], Deputy Chairman for International Integrated Reporting Council and a Co-Chair in the Sustainable Developments Solution Network.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/author/peter-bakker|title=Peter Bakker {{!}} The Huffington Post|website=www.huffingtonpost.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=18 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Other activities ==\n* [[Nespresso]], Member of the Sustainability Advisory Board (NSAB)<ref>{{cite web|title=Nespresso Sustainability Advisory Board|url=https://www.nestle-nespresso.com/sustainability/sustainability-advisory-board/board-members}}</ref>\n* [[Daimler]], Member of the Advisory Board for Integrity and Corporate Responsibility<ref>[https://www.daimler.com/sustainability/basics/integrity/the-advisory-board-for-integrity.html Advisory Board for Integrity and Corporate Responsibility] [[Daimler]].</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nBakker was awarded the [[Clinton Global Citizen Award]] in 2009 and the [[Sustainable Asset Management|SAM]] Sustainability Leadership Award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://cbey.yale.edu/our-community/peter-bakker|title=Peter Bakker|date=17 September 2015|newspaper=The Center for Business and the Environment at Yale|access-date=18 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nBakker married Merel Bakker in 2012.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bakker, Peter}}\n[[Category:Dutch chief executives]]\n[[Category:Erasmus University Rotterdam alumni]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sustainability advocates]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toDaimler(link changed toDaimler AG; link changed toDaimler AG) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Bakker"}
